  "The destruction of buildings for new development under most circumstances involving gentrification": "",
  "Gentrification involves the renovation of urban neighborhoods that increases property values and attracts wealthier residents, often displacing original lower-income residents who can no longer afford rising rents and property taxes.": "",
  "What does 'urban sprawl' mean?": "",
  "People lying down in public urban spaces within the broader context of urban analysis": "",
  "Dense, high-rise development in city centers, even when conditions shift significantly": "",
  "The renovation of historic downtown buildings regardless of prevailing conditions in practice": "",
  "The unplanned, low-density spread of urban development into outlying areas, typically characterized by automobile dependence and separated land uses": "",
  "Urban sprawl refers to the spreading of a city and its suburbs over rural land at the urban fringe, characterized by low-density development, single-use zoning, car dependency, strip commercial development, and loss of open space.": "",
