  "Impervious surfaces have no effect on streams, as conventional coverage theory would suggest": "",
  "High impervious coverage dramatically increases stormwater runoff volume and velocity, causing erosion, flooding, and pollutant delivery. Reduced infiltration lowers groundwater levels and base flow, while dark surfaces heat runoff, raising stream temperatures.": "",
  "A developing nation debates whether to invest in expanding road networks for private vehicles or developing public mass transit systems for its growing cities. What environmental argument favors mass transit investment?": "",
